    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.1115A/756½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 29, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 29—5:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>947. For the President and the Secretary. In view of the certainty that Italy
                    will enter the war during the first week of June unless we send the Atlantic
                    Fleet to Tangier, it would be folly to permit the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington</hi> to enter the Mediterranean.</p>
                <p>I consider it inhuman and indecent to refuse to permit embarkation on the <hi
                        rend="italic">Washington</hi>, after all Americans are embarked, of aliens
                    who have fulfilled all visa requirements and I trust that before the <hi
                        rend="italic">Washington</hi> arrives in Bordeaux you will have authorized
                    me to permit the embarkation of carefully selected aliens who have every right
                    to seek refuge in our country. I can assure you that I will use such authority
                    with discretion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
